## onReady function
The `onReady()` function is a callback provided by the ElavonLightbox component. It is triggered after the lightbox initialization process completes, allowing you to check whether the component loaded successfully or encountered an error.
**When to use onReady()**
- Verify successful initialization.
- Handle initialization errors gracefully, such as:
- Displaying an error message to the user.
- Logging the error for debugging or monitoring.
## Syntax
```javascript
function onReady(error) {
// Custom logic based on initialization result
}
```
## Parameters
| Parameter
|
Type
|
Description |
|----------|-------------|:------|
| error | boolean | Indicates whether an error occurred during initialization. `true = error, false = success`. |
## Example usage
:::code-block
```javascript
function onReady(error) {
if (error) {
console.error("Lightbox failed to initialize.");
} else {
lightbox.show();
}
}
```
:::

