## show function
The `show()` function is a method of the ElavonLightbox instance that displays the lightbox UI component. This component is a secure, embedded modal designed to allow shoppers to interact with the payment form and complete transactions in a PCI-compliant environment.
Calling `show()` initiates the payment experience by rendering the lightbox over your existing page content.
**When to use show()**
- The lightbox has been successfully initialized.
## Syntax
```javascript
lightbox.show();
```
## Example usage
:::code-block
```javascript
function onReady(error) {
if (error) {
console.error("Lightbox failed to initialize.");
} else {
lightbox.show();
}
}
```
:::
